    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="888"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 253, of
                    November 18, 1910, transmitting a note<note n="1" xml:id="d888fn3">This refers
                        to the communication to the Minister for Foreign Affairs; there was no other
                        inclosure.</note> from the department of government stating that in future
                    foreigners in Mexican prisons may communicate with the diplomatic and consular
                    officers of their respective countries.</p>
                <p>I inclose for your information a copy of an instruction which the Department has
                    addressed to the minister at Guatemala City<note n="2" xml:id="d888fn2">See <ref
                            target="#pg_275">page 275</ref>.</note> requesting him to make
                    representations to the President of Guatemala, with a view to bringing about a
                    similar modification of the system of “incomunicación” which prevails in that
                    country.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
